{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T03:51:46.924Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Distance Metrics"}, {"type": "text", "text": " are mathematical functions that quantify "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "how similar or different"}, {"type": "text", "text": " two data points are in feature space — they determine which points are \"nearest neighbors\" in k-NN and influence decision boundaries in SVMs (especially with RBF kernels)."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What They Are"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Distance metrics measure "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "closeness"}, {"type": "text", "text": " between data points by calculating the distance across feature dimensions:"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "In "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "k-NN"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Metric determines which training examples are the \"k nearest neighbors\""}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "In "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "SVMs"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Used in RBF (Radial Basis Function) kernels to compare examples via distance"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "No single \"best\" metric"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Choice depends on data type, dimensionality, and problem"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Why they're important in k-NN"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Impacts how neighbors are selected and ranked\n- Influences decision boundaries created by classifier\n- Improves handling of various data types (continuous, categorical)\n- Reduces misclassification in high-dimensional spaces\n- Ensures fair comparison when features vary in scale"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common Distance Metrics"}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Distance Metrics — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Euclidean Distance"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (L2 Norm)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Most common"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for k-NN — straight-line distance between two points in continuous space."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Formula"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n$$d(p, q) = \\sqrt{\\sum"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "{i=1}^{n} (p_i - q_i)^2}$$"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Where:\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "p"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " and "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "q"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = data points\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "n"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = number of dimensions (features)\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "p_i, q_i"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = value of dimension "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "i"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " for each point"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Properties"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- ✅ Sensitive to large differences in feature values\n- ✅ Performs well on low-dimensional, normalized data\n- ✅ Commonly used for geometric interpre